The paper deals with the problem of distributed computation, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Distributed Computing (cs.DC), and Computer Communication (cs.CC). The problem also involves the use of algorithms, which is a topic in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the error probability and error exponent, which are concepts related to Statistical Learning (cs.SI).
